    <autolevel level="3"><feature optional="YES"><name>Level 3: Artificer Subclass: Alchemist</name>
        <text>Craft Magic Elixirs and Potions.

An Alchemist is an expert at combining reagents to produce magical effects. Alchemists use their creations to give life and to leech it away.

Source:	Eberron: Forge of the Artificer</text>
      </feature>
    </autolevel>
    <autolevel level="3"><feature optional="YES"><name>Level 3: Tools of the Trade (Alchemist)</name>
        <text>You gain the following benefits:
	• Tool Proficiency: You gain proficiency with Alchemist's Supplies and the Herbalism Kit. If you already have one of these proficiencies, you gain proficiency with one other type of Artisan's Tools of your choice (or with two other types if you have both).
	• Potion Crafting: When you brew a potion using the crafting rules, the amount of time required to craft it is halved.

Source:	Eberron: Forge of the Artificer</text>
      </feature>
    </autolevel>
    <autolevel level="3"><feature optional="YES"><name>Level 3: Alchemist Spells (Alchemist)</name>
        <text>When you reach an Artificer level specified in the Alchemist Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.

Alchemist Spells
Level | Spells
3 | Healing Word, Ray of Sickness
5 | Flaming Sphere, Melf's Acid Arrow
9 | Gaseous Form, Mass Healing Word
13 | Death Ward, Vitriolic Sphere
17 | Cloudkill, Raise Dead

Source:	Eberron: Forge of the Artificer</text>
